Gunmen have reportedly shot four persons dead in Kono Boue community in the Khana Local Government Area of Rivers State. The gunmen were said to have invaded the community on Saturday and shot indiscriminately, killing the four victims in the process.  They were said to have shot at any young man in sight with AK-47s. It was learnt that the assailants went away with the mobile phones of some residents. The deceased include one Lekara Bira, 32 and Torka, 40. Spokesperson for the community development committee in the area, Golden Nwibakpo, said the deceased persons were law-abiding.